    "long_instructions": "# Do This:\r\n\r\n1. **Run and Observe:** Run the code and observe what happens. \r\n2. **Validation Testing:** Run the validation test to see if that gives you any insights into the bug.\r\n3. **Debugging Strategies:** Decide which debugging strategy would be useful for this buggy program. \r\n4. **Iterate and Test:** Iteratively refine and test the updates you make to the code.\r\n    \r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: black;\">\r\n<h5><strong>📝 Unit Guide</strong></h5>\r\n\r\nDocument your experience with this debugging challenge:\r\n- What strategy did you use? \r\n- How did it help?\r\n- When might it be most useful in the future?\r\n</div>",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\njoy = Painter()\n\ndef paint_step():\n    joy.painter(\"red\")\n    joy.move()\n    joy.pant(\"green\")  \n\npaint_step()\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
    },
    "teacher_markdown": "**Error Type**: Syntax Error (Code won’t run due to a typo)\r\n\r\n**Expected Outcome**: The painter should move forward and paint a red and green tile.\r\n\r\nDebugging Challenge\r\n\r\n- The program throws an AttributeError because .painter() and .pant() are not a valid Painter methods.\r\n- Students must determine what’s wrong with these method calls and correct them.\r\n- Hint for students: Carefully check function and method names.",
    "bubble_choice_description": "You’re sure you wrote everything correctly, but your program refuses to run. There’s an issue hiding in plain sight—something small but critical is causing everything to break. Can you spot the problem?",
